						<div class="postbody">Yeah lidnariq is right.  That's the downfall of arduino often times.  I was able to get an atmega to emulate the controller's shift register but I did that in assembly.  I've had success in programming timing sensitive things in C but made use of the IDE's cycle counter.  I don't think such high level tools are available to arduino...</div>

